I went through every one of these responses looking to make a fat executable JAR file containing all dependencies and none of them worked right.  The answer is the shade plugin, its very easy and straightforward.

    &lt;plugin&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-shade-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;2.3&lt;/version&gt;

      &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;!-- Run shade goal on package phase --&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
          &lt;phase&gt;package&lt;/phase&gt;
          &lt;goals&gt;
            &lt;goal&gt;shade&lt;/goal&gt;
          &lt;/goals&gt;

          &lt;configuration&gt;
            &lt;transformers&gt;
              &lt;transformer implementation=&quot;org.apache.maven.plugins.shade.resource.ManifestResourceTransformer&quot;&gt;
                &lt;mainClass&gt;path.to.MainClass&lt;/mainClass&gt;
              &lt;/transformer&gt;
            &lt;/transformers&gt;
          &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
      &lt;/executions&gt;

    &lt;/plugin&gt;

Be aware that your dependencies need to have a scope of compile or runtime for this to work properly.

[This example came from mkyong.com][1]

  [1]: http://www.mkyong.com/maven/create-a-fat-jar-file-maven-shade-plugin/

